				\begin{document}$${\text{SA}}\left( \lambda \right) = {\text{A}}\left( \lambda \right) \times {\text{SS}}\left( \lambda \right),$$\end{document} where A(λ) stands for the values of absorptance at each wavelength (λ) and SS(λ) stands for the solar spectrum intensities at each wavelength (λ). The unit of this parameter was expressed as W m−2.

With the same solar spectrum, it was also calculated the effective solar radiation (eSS) of each action spectrum analyzed (Act.Sp.) as:eSSλ=SSλ×Act.Sp.λ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
